<paragraph blockId="6.[131,775,1424,1709]" box="[132,251,1424,1455]" pageId="6" pageNumber="221">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[131,775,1424,1709]" lastBlockId="6.[811,1455,598,720]" pageId="6" pageNumber="221">
<taxonomicName authority="Tran, 2021" authorityName="V. T. Tran" authorityYear="2021" box="[132,325,1459,1485]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bambusa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="6" pageNumber="221" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nghiana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[132,325,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="221">Bambusa nghiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[332,416,1459,1485]" pageId="6" pageNumber="221" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is placed in subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[663,775,1460,1485]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bambusa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="6" pageNumber="221" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Lingnania">
<emphasis box="[663,775,1460,1485]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="221">Lingnania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the characters of culm internodes long, branches usually absent on lower culm, flowers purple. Otherwise, this species may be close to 
<taxonomicName box="[306,514,1554,1580]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bambusa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="6" pageNumber="221" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gurgandii">
<emphasis box="[306,514,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="221">Bambusa gurgandii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species discovered in Khe Tre area, Nam Dong District, Thua Thien Hue Province. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[351,485,1618,1644]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bambusa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="6" pageNumber="221" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gurgandii">
<emphasis box="[351,485,1618,1644]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="221">B. gurgandii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in basal part at the sheath insertion with a narrow ring-like band of dense spreading hairs, large auricles protruding. However, the new species differs from the latter by having long internode, blade with non spreading lobe-like auricles, auricles upcurved at the end, 2-4 perfect flowers, one terminal vestigial flower. Differences are summarised in 
<tableCitation box="[1119,1202,693,720]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="6.[389,400,219,236]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="TABLE 1. — Comparison of Bambusa nghiana sp. nov. with Bambusa gurgandii K.M.Wong &amp; Diep." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF306628FFDBE07DD5EEFF50FB2A65E4" pageId="6" pageNumber="221" tableUuid="DF306628FFDBE07DD5EEFF50FB2A65E4">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
